	 <summary><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px">Your customer is in the "deciding to trial" phase of the prescribing cycle. Setting clear expectations about insurance coverage is the best way to handle Dr. Bennett’s concern at this stage and to close on this phase of the prescribing cycle. If you choose to offer a creative solution to resolve his concerns (Choice A), you are jumping ahead to the next phase of the prescribing cycle, without closing on this phase. You have already worked through fair balance and have helped Dr. Bennett evaluate all his options, so Choice C is not the ideal way to respond, either. Choice D is an okay choice, but you should have already planned out your targets for this customer on a value map, so this may or may not resolve the current concerns they have. Choice B is the best choice.</welcomeText>]]></summary>
